'I don't know if I want to eat one of those things.' The woman in threadbare boots grimaced at the hard-shelled creatures.

The woman in a grey cloak put on a smug smile. 'Yes you do. You just don't know it yet.'

'They look like they'll be crunchy.'

'You remove the shell, you dolt. The meat inside is as sweet and tender as anything you've ever had.'

'They're scary to look at,' Threadbare Boots said.

'Then don't look at them,' Grey Cloak retorted, her patience cleaving paper thin. 'Trust me, a little butter and some sour fruit and you'll be happy as a clam.'

'I don't like clams either.'
Oversized crabs have taken over the beach of Baj Khatûg east of Zamarzîr.\n\nDefeat crabs.
Large crabs roam a beach on the north-east side of Halrax.
